Gauteng Premier David Makhura has appointed Deputy Legislature Speaker Dikgang “Uhuru” Moiloa. Moiloa is a replacement for former Human Settlements, Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs MEC Paul Mashatile. Mashatile was elected as ANC Treasure-General during the December Elective conference in Nasrec, a post that requires him to be at the ANC headquarters full time. Moiloa will be sworn in on Friday. He has among other previous roles been ANC Gauteng PEC member since 1998 and has also played numerous roles in the Gauteng legislature. Amongst them, as Housing Committee Chairperson, Chairperson of Economic Development Committee and also a Committee of Chairpersons. -TNA Reporter